Zalman Orlianski's family has confirmed that he died in a Johannesburg hospital on Sunday night. JOHANNESBURG - A 71-year-old man involved in an altercation with an Uber driver at OR Tambo International Airport has succumbed to his wounds. Zalman Orlianski's family has confirmed that he died in a Johannesburg hospital on Sunday night. It is understood that Orlianski and the driver had an argument over a parking space, which turned violent. Uber has since removed the man from its service and says that he has been arrested.